'''John T. Korsmo''' is a former chair of the [[Federal Housing Finance Board]] who [[plea|pled]] guilty to lying to congress.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bismarcktribune.com/articles/2005/03/23/news/update/upd06.txt|title=Former Housing Board Chairman Agrees to Plead Guilty|date=Mar 23, 2005|publisher=The [[Bismark Tribune]]|author=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref>

In 1992 Korsmo ran as a [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] to represent [[North Dakota]] in the [[United States House of Representatives|House of Representatives]], but lost the elections to [[Earl Pomeroy]] by a 57% to 39% margin.

